Reasoning: The paper discusses wireless powered communication networks, which are a combination of wireless communication and energy harvesting. This topic falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a novel transmission scheme for optimal allocation of power and time to maximize network throughput. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses wireless networks and their operation. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the control of power and time allocation in the network. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses the transmission of information. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a practical solution for a wireless network scenario.
